cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with adversarial examples in computer vision models and their effect on human observers. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves human perception and cognition, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The use of transfer learning techniques and machine learning models indicates that it could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the security and robustness of computer vision models, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper involves the use of adversarial examples, which could also classify it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
